So far it's helpful! The quizzes are only 10 questions long, so it's a quick way to squeeze in studying on your lunch break or while you wait for the bus. I would love to see: - A greater variety of questions within each topic. Some quizzes have the same scenario multiple times, with slightly different questions. - If the best quiz score could be displayed beside each topic or if there were more than 2 colors (orange/green) for completed topics. With the current system, a topic is only green if you score a 10/10. All scores before that are an orange/red color. More colors or posted scores would help users prioritize areas to go back and study. For example, if I scored a 5/10 on one quiz and an 8 or 9/10 on another, I would want to review the topics and retake the 5/10 quiz first. Depending on time, I may not even bother retaking the 9/10 quiz.

content: I don't trust the answers after finding incorrect responses, which makes this tool ineffective, frustrating, and untrustworthy.
